longBusinessSummary: Grangex AB operates as a mineral development company, engages in identifies, acquires, and develops portfolio of mineral projects in Europe. It primarily explores for lead, phosphate, and iron ores. The company owns Dannemora mine located in Östhammar; and the Apatite project located in Grängesberg. Grangex AB was incorporated in 2006 and is headquartered in Stockholm, Sweden.
